<TEXT><BODY>
<DIV1 TYPE="text">
<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="114r">
<SP><SPEAKER>[question]</SPEAKER>
<P>Frend in crist as seynt poule sei&thorn;&middot; We ne hauen
 here no cyte&middot; &thorn;at is dwelling&middot; but we sechen
 on &thorn;at is to come here after&middot;<NOTE>He 13.14</NOTE> And &thorn;erfore me
 &thorn;inke&thorn; &thorn;at we schulden ben longyng &thorn;iderward
 alle &thorn;e tyme of oure lyf&middot; wi&thorn; al oure power&middot; Si&thorn;
 we han no rest ne non abydyng but &thorn;ere&middot; But
 more harme is I knowe no&yogh;t a ri&yogh;t &thorn;e weye <DEL>&thorn;e</DEL>
 <DEL>weye</DEL> toward &thorn;is place&middot; &amp; &thorn;erfore I preye &thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;ou
 telle me &thorn;e weye toward &thorn;is place&middot;</P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[answer]</SPEAKER>
 <P>Dere frend
 oure lord &amp; oure mayster iesu crist seyde to his
 disciples &thorn;at he hym siluen is the weye toward
 heuene &amp; he is tru&thorn;e &thorn;at lede&thorn; vs sykurly in
 oure weye &amp; he is <DEL>sykurly</DEL> lyf &thorn;at make&thorn; vs
 lyue in soule w<ADD>h</ADD>yles we ben in &thorn;is world&middot;<NOTE>Jn 14.6</NOTE> &amp; after
 &thorn;at lyf he wil bringe vs to ablisful lif &thorn;at
 schal lasten withouten ende bo&thorn;e in body &amp; in soule&middot;</P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[question]</SPEAKER>
 <P> frend or &thorn;an &thorn;ou passe fer&thorn;er I preye &thorn;e what is
 &thorn;at lyf of soule &amp; telle whe&thorn;ir alle men han
 &thorn;is lif&middot;</P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[answer]</SPEAKER>
 <P>&para;Sire aman is made to &thorn;re manere of
 liues &para; &thorn;e first lif is &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e body&middot; &amp; &thorn;is
 lif han bo&thorn;e goodemen &amp; schrewis&middot;//&para;&thorn;e secun|de lif is of &thorn;e soule&middot; &amp; &thorn;at is to lyuen out
 of synne &para;Of &thorn;is lif crist speke&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel
 &thorn;er as he sei&thorn; but aman be born eft sones he
 ne may not entren in to &thorn;e kyngdom&middot; of heue|ne&middot;//<NOTE>Jn 3.3</NOTE></P>
 <P>&para;&thorn;e first bering of aman is&middot&middot; whan he is
 I born in to a bodyliche lyuyng of his moder
 wombe&middot; But he is borun eft sones of water

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="114v">

&amp; of &thorn;e holygost into a lyf of soule&middot; And &thorn;at be|ryng is whan a child or a man is I fulled&middot&middot; &amp; vn|derfonge&thorn; cristene mennes be leue&middot; &amp; for sake&thorn; &thorn;e
 deuel &amp; his werkes &thorn;at ben synnes //&para;And &thorn;is
 lif of soule mankynde hadde no&yogh;t from &thorn;e tyme
 &thorn;at adam hadde I synned in paradys in to &thorn;e comyng
 of crist&middot; for as seynt poule sei&thorn;&middot; Deth regnede
 from adam to moyses&middot;<NOTE>Ro 5.14</NOTE> &amp; synne regnede from
 moyses in to &thorn;e tyme of grace &thorn;at was I &yogh;eue be
 crist&middot; &para;Ne al &thorn;e ri&yogh;twisnes of alle &thorn;e olde lawe
 ne sacrifices &thorn;at weren I doon for mannes synne
 ne prechyng ne preeyer of prophetes ne of prestes ne
 mi&yogh;t not make man kynde clene of <ADD>his</ADD> synne</P>
 <P> &para;And &thorn;erfore oure fadur of heuene sente his ow|ne sone adoun in to &thorn;e er&thorn;e to fulfille &thorn;e lawe
 &amp; &thorn;e prophetes &amp; so he dide&middot; for &thorn;er as a man ne
 myhte no&thorn;er be &thorn;e lawe ne be &thorn;e prophetes ben
 I iustified of his synne&middot; he of his grace &amp; no&yogh;t
 of oure ri&yogh;twisnes&middot; ne of oure disseruyng&middot;
 for &yogh;af alle &thorn;ilk men her synnes &thorn;at bi leue|den in hym &amp; brou&yogh;te hem from de&thorn; of syn|ne in to lif of soule&middot;</P>
 <P>for as crist sei&thorn; who &thorn;at
 be leue&thorn; in me &thorn;of he be ded he schal lyue &amp;
 who &thorn;at lyue&thorn; &amp; be leue&thorn; in me&middot&middot; he schal ne|uere dye<NOTE>Jn 11.25-26</NOTE> &amp; who &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;is lif of soule&middot; whyles
 he is in &thorn;is world&middot; he schal come after &thorn;at
 he is ded to an endeles lif of blis bo&thorn;e in bo|dy &amp; in soule&middot; and seynt poule sei&thorn;/ alle disee|ses &thorn;at we mown suffre in &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at now
 is&middot; ne be not wor&thorn;i to &thorn;e blisse &thorn;at is to comen
 here aftur &amp; schal be schewed in vs<NOTE>Ro 8.18</NOTE> / &amp; &thorn;erfore
 he sei&thorn; nou&thorn;er de&thorn; ne lyf ne angeres <SUPPLIED>?read: angeles</SUPPLIED> ne

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="115r">

tribulaciouns / ne no &thorn;ing &thorn;at now is / ne &thorn;at is gonne&middot; ne
 &thorn;at is to comen her after&middot;&middot; may departen vs from
 &thorn;e charite &thorn;at is in iesu crist&middot;<NOTE>Ro 8.38-39</NOTE></P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[question]</SPEAKER>
  <P>&para;frend as me &thorn;inke&thorn;
 <DEL>&thorn;is lif of soule</DEL> &thorn;is lif of soule &thorn;at is for sakyng
 of synne&middot;&middot; is &thorn;e ri&yogh;t weye to heuene&middot; but we ben
 ful vnstabul &amp; ful vnconyng to go &thorn;is weye&middot; &amp; we
 han strong temptaciouns &amp; strong enemyes&middot; as &thorn;e de|uel &amp; &thorn;e world &amp; oure owne fleshe &thorn;at euere more temp|te&thorn; vs to synne&middot; &para;And &thorn;er fore we moten putte vs
 fulliche in &thorn;e mercy of god&middot; &amp; &thorn;of we lyue not so per|fytliche as he tau&yogh;t vs&middot&middot; &amp; as he lyuede hym silf
 we hopen to ben saued&middot; for he sei&thorn; hym self who
 &thorn;at be leue&thorn; &amp; is cristened schal be sauid<NOTE>Mk 16.16</NOTE></P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[answer]</SPEAKER>
 <P>&para;Sir in
 summe &thorn;inges &yogh;e seye ful so&thorn;e/bot it is not al so&thorn;e
 as &yogh;e hopen in &yogh;owre seying&middot; So&thorn;e it is &thorn;at &thorn;e ri&yogh;t
 weye to heuene is for sakyng of synne&middot; &amp; &thorn;er
 come&thorn; no man to heuene&middot&middot; but he go &thorn;is wey&middot; and
 forsakynge of synne&middot; is no more but &thorn;e kepyng
 of goddis hestis &amp; of his wordis &amp; leuyng alle
 &thorn;ilk &thorn;inges &thorn;at god forbede&thorn; &para;And soth it is &thorn;at
 &thorn;is is an hard wey &amp; a streyt&middot; for as crist sei&thorn;
 it is a streyt weye &thorn;at lede&thorn; a man to <DEL>heuene</DEL> lif
 &amp; fewe &thorn;er ben &thorn;at fynden &thorn;at weye &amp; a brode
 wey it is &thorn;at lede&thorn; aman to perdicioun &amp; to deth &amp;
 ful many &thorn;er ben &thorn;at fynden &thorn;ilk weye<NOTE>Mt 7.13-14</NOTE> ful so&thorn;e
 it is also &thorn;at we ben vnstable &amp; vncunnyng &amp;
 &thorn;at we han strong enemyes &amp; strong temptaciouns
 also &para;But it is certeyn &yogh;if we desire wisdome
 of god &amp; stabulnes to a&yogh;enstonde synne&middot; god wil
 &yogh;euen vs &thorn;at we axen&middot; so &thorn;at we axen trustiliche
 &para;ffor crist sei&thorn; / &yogh;e &thorn;at ben wicked &amp; yuul wollen &yogh;euen
 &yogh;oure childeren good &thorn;inges whan &thorn;ei axen &yogh;ow gode&middot;
 &amp; myche more wille &yogh;oure heuenliche fadur &yogh;euen

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="115v">

hem a goode spiri&yogh;t &thorn;at axen hit of h<DEL>e</DEL>im<NOTE>Lk 1.13</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;erfore
 he sei&thorn; seche&thorn; &amp; &yogh;e schullen ifynde&middot; axeth &amp; &yogh;e schul|len vnderfongen&middot; knocke&thorn; at &thorn;e dore &amp; I schal open
 hit to &yogh;ow&middot;<NOTE>Lk 1.9</NOTE> And seynt Jame sei&thorn; who &thorn;at nede&thorn; wis|dome&middot; axe hit of god &thorn;at &yogh;eue&thorn; al men plenteuosly|che&middot; &amp; <DEL>oben</DEL> obre<ADD>i</ADD>de&thorn; no man of &thorn;at he schal &yogh;euen
 hym&middot; but axe he trustiliche &amp; haue no dou&yogh;te&middot; for he
 &thorn;at dou&yogh;te&thorn; in his axyng is lyche &thorn;e flood of &thorn;e see
 &thorn;at is meued &amp; I born abou&yogh;te wi&thorn; &thorn;e wynd &amp; &thorn;ere|fore suche aman ne trowe he nou&yogh;t &thorn;at he schal vn|derfongen any &thorn;ing of god&middot;<NOTE>Jas 1.5-7</NOTE> And he sei&thorn; &thorn;at man is
 I blessed &thorn;at abyde&thorn; temptacioun&middot; for whan he is I pre|uid he schal vndurfong acroune of lif &thorn;at god
 hath be hote to &thorn;ilk &thorn;at louen hym ne no man
 whan he is I tempted seye &thorn;at <DEL>louen</DEL> he is I tempted
 of god&middot; for he ne is no temptour of yuul ne he temp|te&thorn; no man&middot&middot; but eueryche man is tempted of his
 owne coueytyng&middot; &amp; whan coueytyng &thorn;at hath con|ceyued / hit brynge&thorn; forth synne &amp; whan &thorn;e synne
 is brou&yogh;t to &thorn;e ende hit engendere&thorn; de&thorn;&middot;<NOTE>Jas 1.12-15</NOTE></P>
 <P>Of &thorn;es wor|des sire &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t &thorn;en <DEL>mi&yogh;t</DEL> I seen  &thorn;at hit ne is but
 oure defau&yogh;te &thorn;at we <DEL>he</DEL> ne han cunnyng &amp; stabul|nes to a&yogh;eyn stonde oure temptaciouns&middot; and &thorn;of we han
 strong enemyes &amp; grete temptaciouns hit ne is but
 oure owne vnkyndenes &amp; wickednesse &thorn;at we fal|len in to synne&middot; for god suffere&thorn; no man to ben i-|tempted passyng his mi&yogh;t&middot; and alle &thorn;e deuels in
 helle ne alle &thorn;e might of &thorn;e world ne of mannes
 flesche ne mown not maken aman / ne a womman
 breken godis hestys a&yogh;ens his wille&middot; for god ha&thorn;
 I &yogh;euen aman afre wil/ &amp; ha&thorn; I sette be forun hym
 bo&thorn;e good &amp; yuul lif &amp; deth&middot; blessyng&middot; &amp; cursyng&middot;

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="116r">

&amp; aman may chese whe&thorn;er of &thorn;es he wil take&middot; And &yogh;if
 aman is buxum to his god &amp; kepi&thorn; his hestis&middot; &thorn;anne
 he chese&thorn; good lif &amp; blessyng&middot; and &yogh;if he for sake&thorn;
 &thorn;e hestis of god &thorn;an he chese&thorn; yuul &amp; deth&middot; &amp; &thorn;e cur|syng of god&middot; as moyses sei&thorn; in &thorn;e first boke of olde
 lawe &para;And daui&thorn; sei&thorn; in &thorn;e sauter&middot; alle &thorn;es ben a|cursed &thorn;at bowen a wey from &thorn;i hestis&middot; &thorn;anne it is
 bot oure owne folye &amp; <ADD>oure</ADD> owne vnkyndenes &thorn;at we fal|len in to synne&middot;</P>
 <P>Soth it is also &thorn;at we moten alle put|ten vs in &thorn;e mercy of god&middot; &amp; not axen heuene &thorn;oru ry&yogh;t|fulnes&middot; iustifying oure self before god&middot; for dauid
 sei&thorn; in &thorn;e sauter&middot; Eueriche lyuyng man schal
 not ben iustified in &thorn;i si&yogh;t&middot;<NOTE>Ps 142.2 Vulg.</NOTE> But na&thorn;ereles no man
 hop to come to heuene but if he leue synne&middot; no&thorn;er
 for &thorn;e be leue &thorn;at he ha&thorn; in crist&middot; ne for &thorn;e grete mercy
 of god&middot; for as seynt jame sei&thorn; deueles in helle be-|leuen &amp; dreden&middot;<NOTE>Jas 2.19</NOTE> &amp; he sei&thorn; ri&yogh;t as a body is ded wi&thorn;|outen spiri&yogh;t&middot; ri&yogh;t fei&thorn; &amp; beleue is ded wi&thorn; outen
 good werkes&middot;<NOTE>Jas 2.26</NOTE> And <ADD>seynt</ADD> jon sei&thorn;&middot; who &thorn;at sei&thorn; <DEL>&thorn;at sei&thorn;</DEL>
 &thorn;at he knowe&thorn; god &amp; kepi&thorn; not his hestes&middot; he
 is a lyere&middot;<NOTE>1 Jn 2.4</NOTE> &amp; crist sei&thorn; w<ADD>h</ADD>arto clepe &yogh;e me lord lord
 &amp; do&thorn; <ADD>no&yogh;t</ADD> &thorn;ilke &thorn;inges &thorn;at I sey&yogh;e<NOTE>Lk 6.46</NOTE> and he sei&thorn; also
 al &thorn;ilke &thorn;at sey&yogh;en to me lord lord ne schul not
 entren in to &thorn;e kyngdome of heuene&middot; but he &thorn;at
 do&thorn; &thorn;e wille of my fader &thorn;at is in heuene&middot; he schal
 entren in to &thorn;e kyngdom of heuene/and he sei&thorn;
 also in &thorn;at day many schul come &amp; seyn lord ha|ue we no&yogh;t I caste fendes ou&yogh;t of men in &thorn;i name&middot;
 &amp; ne haue we no&para;t iprophecyed in &thorn;i name <ADD>&amp; i-doon many tokenes in &thorn;i name&middot;</ADD> And crist
 sei&thorn; &thorn;at he wil &thorn;anne seye to hem&middot; I ne knew
 &yogh;ow neuere&middot; go&thorn; awey from me alle &thorn;at wurchen
 wickednes&middot;<NOTE>Mt 7.21-23</NOTE> &amp; crist sei&thorn; also &thorn;at mannes sone wil

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="116v">

come &amp; deme eueriche man aftir his werkis&middot; &amp; &thorn;i|lk &thorn;at han wil I lyued schullen comen to &thorn;e blis
 of heuene&middot; &amp; &thorn;e o&thorn;er &thorn;at han continued her lif in
 synne schul gon to &thorn;e euere lastynge peynes of
 helle &thorn;at ben I ordeyned for &thorn;e deuel &amp; his seruaun|tes&middot;</P>
 <P>And gode sire what schal cristes passioun or
 &thorn;e schedyng of his blood in &thorn;e whyche blood &thorn;ou art
 i cristened &amp; I clensed of &thorn;i synne stonde &thorn;e to profi&yogh;t
 but &thorn;ou leue &thorn;i synne &amp; kepe goddis hestes&middot; In
 certeyn seynt petre sei&thorn;&middot; it were better for aman
 &thorn;at he knew not &thorn;e wey of trewthe&middot; &thorn;an after
 his knewing turnen a&yogh;eyn to synne&middot; for as he sei&thorn;
 such men ben I lyche swyne &thorn;at whan &thorn;ei ben cle|ne gon in to a slowe &amp; maken hem fouler &thorn;anne &thorn;ei
 weren &amp; he sei&thorn; also &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben liche houndes&middot; &thorn;at
 kaste&thorn; vp &thorn;e mete &thorn;at &thorn;ei han eete &amp; sithen tur|nen hem a&yogh;en&middot; &amp; eten &thorn;at &thorn;ei casten&middot;<NOTE>2 Pe 2.21-22</NOTE> &para;And for &thorn;es
 foule maners of swyn &amp; of houndes crist seyde to his
 disciples&middot; Ne &yogh;eue &yogh;e not holy &thorn;inges to houndes ne
 cast &yogh;e not margeri perles be fore swyn&middot; last &thorn;ei de|foulen hem wi&thorn; here feet &amp; &thorn;e houndes turnen hem
 &amp; al to tere &yogh;ow&middot;<NOTE>Mt 7.6</NOTE></P></SP>
 <SP><SPEAKER>[question]</SPEAKER>
 <P>frend now I se &thorn;at &thorn;e ri&yogh;t weye to
 heuene is lif of soule in forsakyng synne&middot; &amp; ke|ping goddes hestes&middot; &amp; I see wil &thorn;at eueryche man
 may leuen synne if he wole him seluen&middot; &amp; I see
 wele &thorn;a no man schal be saued but he leue his syn|ne&middot; No&thorn;er for &thorn;e grete mercy of god&middot; ne for &thorn;e be le|ue &thorn;at a man ha&thorn; in god&middot; ne for his cristenyng
 but if he haue goode werkes&middot; But frende how
 schullen &yogh;ung childeren ben I saued &thorn;at ben i-|cristened&middot; &amp; si&thorn;e dyen or &thorn;an &thorn;ei ben of age to
 knowe godes hestes</P></SP>

 <SP><SPEAKER>[answer]</SPEAKER>
 <P>&para;Sire &yogh;e wyte&thorn; wil &thorn;at whan

<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="117r">

a child is I cristened&middot; he receyue&thorn; his byleue by mene
 persones&middot; for &thorn;at tyme no&thorn;er he ha&thorn; knowyng whyche
 his be leue is / ne mi&yogh;t forto speke whyche is his
 be leue&middot; &amp; ri&yogh;t as <SUPPLIED>he</SUPPLIED> vndirfonge&thorn; his be leue by me|ne persones&middot; ri&yogh;t so be &thorn;o same mene he forsaki&thorn; &thorn;e de|uel &amp; his werkes &amp; by hote&thorn; to ben buxum to god
 &amp; to kepen his hestes &amp; so &thorn;e child is saued &thorn;oru
 &thorn;e be leue&middot; &thorn;at he vnderfonge&thorn; &amp; &thorn;oru &thorn;e forwa<ADD>r</ADD>d
 &thorn;at he make&thorn; bi &thorn;es mene persones&middot;</P>
 <P>But in certeyn
 a man  or a womman of ful age ne schal not ben
 i-sauyd: but he do&thorn; &thorn;e werkes of his be leue
 &thorn;at is to seyn &thorn;at he kepe goddis hestis &amp; leue syn|ne&middot; for as seynt poule sei&thorn; alle we ben &thorn;at <SUPPLIED>read: &thorn;at ben</SUPPLIED> i-bap|tized in iesu crist&middot; ben i-baptized in his de&thorn;&middot; &amp; we ben
 i-birried wi&thorn; hym in to deth&middot; &thorn;at ri&yogh;t as crist roos
