 <P>&para;And a ful hard
 word sey&thorn; seynt Jame to riche men of &thorn;e world&middot; for he
 sei&thorn; wepe &yogh;e riche men&middot; &amp; make &yogh;e sorewe&middot; for &thorn;e wrec|hednes &thorn;at schal come to &yogh;ow her aftur&middot; &yogh;oure ri|ches is for rotid&middot; &amp; &yogh;owre clo&thorn;es ben i-eten wi&thorn; mo|wtes&middot; &yogh;owre gold &amp; &yogh;ower siluer is i-rustid&middot; &amp; &yogh;owr<UNCLEAR>e</UNCLEAR>
 rust schal ben in wittenissyng to &yogh;ow&middot; &amp; schal ete
 &yogh;oure flesch as fuyr&middot; &yogh;e tresore&thorn; to &yogh;ow &thorn;e wra&thorn;e
 of god in &thorn;e last dayes&middot;<NOTE>Jas 5.1-3</NOTE> wolde god &thorn;at &thorn;ese riche men
 wolden take kepe to seynt poules wordes as he
 sei&thorn;&middot; we browten no &thorn;ing in to &thorn;is world&middot; &amp; it is
 no doute &thorn;at we mowen bere no &thorn;ing hennes &amp;
 &thorn;erfore haue <SUPPLIED>we</SUPPLIED> liflode &amp; helyng be we apayed&middot; for &thorn;ilk
 &thorn;at wilne&thorn; to ben i-maad riche &thorn;ei fallen in to temp|tacioun&middot; &amp; in to &thorn;e deuels grene &amp; in to many vn|profytable desires &amp; noyful &thorn;at drenchen men in-|to de&thorn; &amp; in to perdicioun&middot; for &thorn;e rote of al yuel is co|ueytise&middot; &thorn;e whyche sum men han desired &amp; han i-er|red from her fei&thorn; &amp; han i-brou&yogh;t hem seluen in-|to myche sor<UNCLEAR>e</UNCLEAR><NOTE>1 Tm 6.7-10</NOTE>we &para; And <ADD>he</ADD> bidde&thorn; riche men of &thorn;e
 world &thorn;at &thorn;ei hope not in &thorn;e victorie of richesses but
 in god &thorn;at lyue&thorn;&middot; &thorn;at &yogh;eue&thorn; vs alle &thorn;inges plente|uosliche to vsen hem &amp; to do wil wi&thorn; hem&middot; &amp; to
 ben i-made riche in goode werkes in &yogh;euynge li&yogh;t|liche &amp; in comunyng here goodes to hem&middot; &thorn;at ben
 nedy to maken hem tresour &amp; a good fundement
 here after &thorn;at &thorn;ei mowen hauen &thorn;at lyf &thorn;at
