&thorn;e kyngdome of heuene as he sei&thorn; in certen&middot;<NOTE>Col 3.5</NOTE></P>
<P>&para; Treu|&thorn;e is a no&thorn;er uertu&middot; &thorn;at come&thorn; ou&yogh;t of loue&middot; &amp; norische&thorn;
 loue also&middot; for who &thorn;at loue&thorn; god&middot; he wole loue trew|&thorn;e &amp; be trewe bo&thorn;e in werk &amp; in word&middot; for god hym self
 is treu&thorn;e &amp; endeles trewe&middot; as he sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;e de|uel was mansleere from &thorn;e be gynnyng&middot; &amp; ne ha&thorn;
 not stonden in treu&thorn;e&middot; for treu&thorn;e is not in hym and
 whanne he speke&thorn; <ADD><UNCLEAR>lesing he spekyt</UNCLEAR></ADD> of his owene&middot; for he is alyere &amp; fa|der of lesynges<NOTE>Jn 8.44</NOTE> &para;And si&thorn; crist come to bringe vs ou&yogh;t
 of &thorn;e deueles seruice to ben goddis childeren &amp; his
 seruauntes also&middot; Nedeliche we moten leue alle ma|nere lesynges for crist sei&thorn; who &thorn;at do&thorn; synne&middot; is seruant
 of synne&middot;<NOTE>Jn 8.34</NOTE> and &thorn;anne who &thorn;at make&thorn; lesyng he is
 seruaunt of lesyng&middot; &amp; of &thorn;e deuel &thorn;at is fader of lesynges&middot; But a cristen man &thorn;at is goddis child &amp;
 loue&thorn; hym a bouen alle o&thorn;ere &thorn;inges <ADD>nil do no &thorn;inges</ADD> &thorn;at may de-|parten hym from his fader of heuene&middot; &amp; &thorn;anne
 mout he leuen alle manere lesynges &amp; alle ma|nere falsenesses &para; And for crist wolde &thorn;at his ser|uauntes weren perfy&yogh;t bo&thorn;e in loue &amp; in treu&thorn;e&middot;
 ri&yogh;t as he made an ende of alle maner vntreu&thorn;e
 ri&yogh;t so in his cummyng&middot; he made an ende of o&thorn;es
 &thorn;at neuere weren i-ordeyned&middot; but for defaute of
 treu&thorn;e&middot; for among trewe men nede&thorn; noon o&thorn;es
 &amp; herfore crist sei&thorn;&middot; It was seyd sumtyme&middot; &thorn;ou sch|alt not for swere &thorn;e but &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;elde to god
 &thorn;in o&thorn;es&middot; but I sey &yogh;ow &thorn;at &yogh;e sweren for no &thorn;ing
 not bi heuene&middot; for hit is goddis trone&middot; ne be
 er&thorn;e for hit is &thorn;e stool of his feet&middot; ne bi Ierusa|lem&middot; for hit is a greet kynges citee&middot; Ne swere
 &thorn;ou not be &thorn;in heued for &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t <SUPPLIED>nou&yogh;t</SUPPLIED> make oon whit
 here ne blak&middot; but <SUPPLIED>&yogh;</SUPPLIED>oure word be &yogh;e&middot;&yogh;e&middot;nay&middot;nay&middot; &amp;
 &thorn;at &thorn;at is more &thorn;an &thorn;is is of yuul<NOTE>Mt 5.33-37</NOTE> &para; And seynt

